Abstract = {{The Ca II infrared triplet is one of the few magnetically sensitive
   chromospheric lines available for ground-based observations. We present
   spectropolarimetric observations of the 8498 and 8542 angstrom lines in
   a quiet Sun region near a decaying active region and compare the
