Abstract = {{As the magnetic flux in a pore increases, it grows in radius and the
   magnetic field at its outer edge becomes increasingly inclined to the
   vertical. It is believed that this increased field inclination causes
   filamentary convection to set in and that this new pattern of
   convection eventually develops into the highly fluted azimuthal
   structure of sunspots. The linear instability was investigated in a
   highly idealized Boussinesq model by Tildesley. A non-linear extension
