   151-176). Selecting the most marginal wavenumbers in the problem
   ensures that the analysis is relevant to the behaviour which would be
   observed in an unbounded plane layer. The symmetries of the resulting
   D-4 x T-2-equivariant bifurcation problem play a large role in
   determining the bifurcation structure and explain the appearance of
   interesting phenomena such as drifting solutions (A.M. Rucklidge, M.
   Silber, Bifurcations of periodic orbits with spatio-temporal
